natural medium
Value: a liquid or solid substance or entity that naturally exists, where microorganims are able to grow.

Subject: artificial medium
Value: a culture medium made specifically for the grow, storage, isolation, identification or transportation of microorganisms.

Subject: poor medium
Value: minimal salts plus glycerol and fumarate

Subject: gene variant mutant
Value: a mutant genotype in which one or more genes can have modifications (subtitutions, indels, partial truncations, etc), but they conserve functionality

Subject: OD600
Value: an optical density that specifies the amount of light of 600 nm of wavelenght the bearer is able to transmit

Subject: OD650
Value: an optical density that specifies the amount of light of 650 nm of wavelenght the bearer is able to transmit

Subject: aeration
Value: a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the amount of oxygen or air the bearer contains

Subject: rpoS knockout mutant
Value: a knockout mutant in which the function of ﻿rpoS gene has been disrupted

Subject: lag phase
Value: a growth phase in which growth rate is null

Subject: acceleration phase
Value: a growth phase in wich growth rate increases

Subject: exponential phase
Value: a growth phase in which growth rate is constant

Subject: retardation phase
Value: a growth phase in which growth rate decreases

Subject: stationary phase
Value: a growth phase after retardation phase in which growth rate is null

Subject: phase of decline
Value: a growth phase in which growth rate is negative

Subject: early exponential phase
Value: is a growth phase that is part of exponential phase and that is located between acceleration phase and mid exponential phase

Subject: early stationary phase
Value: a growth phase that is part of stationary phase and locates right after retardation phase

Subject: early to mid exponential phase
Value: is a growth phase that comprises early exponential phase and mid exponential phase

Subject: late exponential phase
Value: is a growth phase that is part of exponential phase and locates between mid exponential phase and retardation phase

Subject: mid exponential phase
Value: growth phase that is part of exponential phase and locates in the middle of the exponential phase

Subject: mid to late exponential phase
Value: is a growth phase that comprises mid exponential phase and late exponential phase

Subject: leuO overexpression mutant
Value: an overexpression mutant in which leuO is expressed at higher levels than in the wild type

Subject: mprA overexpression mutant
Value: an overexpression mutant in which mprA is expressed at higher levels than the wild type

Subject: ammonia fiber expansion corn stover hydrolysate
Value: a hydrolysate prepared from corn stover pretreated by ammonia fiber expansion

Subject: synH medium
Value: an artificial medium with a defined chemical composition designed to mimic AFEX-pretreated corn stover hydrolysate (ACSH)

Subject: lignotoxins medium
Value: an artificial medium made up of inhibitory compounds that are lignin derivatives resulting from pretreatment and enzymatic hydrolysis of lignocellulose (lignotoxins)

Subject: OD536
Value: an optical density that specifies the amount of light of 536 nm of wavelenght the bearer is able to transmit

Subject: OD550
Value: an optical density that specifies the amount of light of 550 nm of wavelenght the bearer is able to transmit

Subject: minimal defined medium
Value: a defined microbiological culture medium that provides the minimum requirements (e.g., inorganic salts, but no amino acids) needed for growth of a particular bacterium or cell.

Subject: agitation
Value: moving back and forth or with an irregular, rapid, or violent action
